					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>How dare Trafigura and Carter-Ruck set themselves above the people.  We are sovereign, and our representatives must be allowed to speak freely.  Newspapers must be allowed to report Parliament freely.  If Trafigura and Carter-Ruck are setting themselves above the law and free speech then they must pay for their transgression - perhaps Parliament could introduce a law, just for them?</p><p>I am heartily sick of reading about expensive libel trials where it seems impossible to say almost anything about rich people because of our draconian libel laws.  Perhaps that could be sorted out, on the side of truth and a proper privacy law.</p>
						
